text0.content: 2010s​Over the last few years, the unemployment​rate and applications have fallen together.

text1.content: Great Recession​During the Great Recession in the​late 2000s, both the unemployment​rate and share of DI applications​surged.

text2.content: 2000s​Unemployment and applications​tracked each other during much​of the 2000s.

text3.content: 1990s​Unemployment rose during the early 1990s​recession, taking applications with it, but​when unemployment fell, applications per​1,000 workers fell slightly.

text4.content: 1980s​As the unemployment rate fell​in mid- and late-1980s, the​share of applications remained​unchanged, then fell in 1988​and 1989.
